{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775856808700,"sessionID":"ses_286b066a1ffeuIkVCINkfD0aS1","part":{"id":"prt_d795072e3001i7EMxwYG8Gqy54","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79506492001p0BghNikOl9TfY","sessionID":"ses_286b066a1ffeuIkVCINkfD0aS1","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":32422,"input":106,"output":188,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":32128}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775856814815,"sessionID":"ses_286b066a1ffeuIkVCINkfD0aS1","part":{"id":"prt_d79508adc001y6TelV8nXoaO65","messageID":"msg_d7950730b0019fDyUHTgFd4l4X","sessionID":"ses_286b066a1ffeuIkVCINkfD0aS1","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775856839608,"sessionID":"ses_286b066a1ffeuIkVCINkfD0aS1","part":{"id":"prt_d7950eb9d001FWVZ1gELjQPUeF","messageID":"msg_d7950730b0019fDyUHTgFd4l4X","sessionID":"ses_286b066a1ffeuIkVCINkfD0aS1","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-5d9bd3e476464a08980e3b2d1e9a69f5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-014 Delta-Spec\n\n## Purpose\nImplement the Valkey storage provider for the AgentCube session store interface, providing a concrete implementation of the Store interface defined in AR-012 using the Valkey key-value store.\n\n## Base Specs\n- AR-012: 会话存储接口定义\n- deployment/client-go.md: Kubernetes client library for runtime API types\n- session-store/design.md: Session store design including Store interface and storage implementations\n- session-store/spec.md: Session store specification with detailed requirements\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey client initialization\nThe system SHALL initialize a Valkey client using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` with configuration from environment variables.\n\n#### Scenario: Basic Valkey client setup\n- **GIVEN** valid `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variables\n- **WHEN** the Valkey store is initialized\n- **THEN** a Valkey client is created with the configured address and password\n- **AND** the client successfully pings the Valkey server\n\n### Requirement: Store interface implementation\nThe system SHALL implement the Store interface using Valkey client for all required methods.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping method implementation\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey connection\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** it returns nil after successful PING command\n\n#### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID implementation\n- **GIVEN** a session key exists in Valkey\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` is called\n- **THEN** it retrieves and unmarshals the SandboxInfo JSON\n- **AND** returns the SandboxInfo struct\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox implementation\n- **GIVEN** a valid SandboxInfo\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** it stores the JSON and updates indices (expiry and last activity) atomically\n- **AND** uses NX (set if not exists) flag to prevent overwrites\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSandbox implementation\n- **GIVEN** a valid SandboxInfo that already exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** it updates the JSON in Valkey\n- **AND** uses XX (set if exists) flag to ensure the session exists\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID implementation\n- **GIVEN** a session key exists in Valkey\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` is called\n- **THEN** it deletes the session key and removes from both indices\n\n#### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n- **GIVEN** multiple sessions with different expiry times\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** it returns sessions with expiry before the specified time\n- **AND** respects the limit parameter\n\n#### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n- **GIVEN** multiple sessions with different last activity times\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** it returns sessions with last activity before the specified time\n- **AND** respects the limit parameter\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity implementation\n- **GIVEN** a valid session ID and activity timestamp\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, id, at)` is called\n- **THEN** it updates the last activity index for the session\n\n### Requirement: Environment variable configuration\nThe system SHALL read and validate Valkey connection parameters from environment variables.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing required environment variables\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\n- **WHEN** Valkey store initialization is attempted\n- **THEN** it returns an error indicating the missing required variable\n\n### Requirement: Optional Valkey configuration\nThe system SHALL support optional Valkey-specific configuration through environment variables.\n\n#### Scenario: Cache configuration\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` is set to \"true\"\n- **WHEN** Valkey store is initialized\n- **THEN** the client is created with cache disabled\n\n#### Scenario: Single client configuration\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` is set to \"true\"\n- **WHEN** Valkey store is initialized\n- **THEN** the client is created with single client mode\n\n### Requirement: Error handling\nThe system SHALL properly handle Valkey errors and convert them to appropriate package-level errors.\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey connection error\n- **GIVEN** Valkey server is unreachable\n- **WHEN** any store operation is called\n- **THEN** it returns a connection error\n\n#### Scenario: Key not found\n- **GIVEN** a session key does not exist in Valkey\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` is called\n- **THEN** it returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Non-existent session update\n- **GIVEN** a session ID that does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** it returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Non-existent session activity update\n- **GIVEN** a session ID that does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n- **THEN** it returns `ErrNotFound`\n\n### Requirement: Validation\nThe system SHALL validate input parameters before performing store operations.\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox nil validation\n- **GIVEN** nil SandboxInfo\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** it returns an error indicating sandbox cannot be nil\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox empty SessionID validation\n- **GIVEN** SandboxInfo with empty SessionID\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** it returns an error indicating session ID cannot be empty\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox zero ExpiresAt validation\n- **GIVEN** SandboxInfo with zero ExpiresAt\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** it returns an error indicating expires at cannot be zero\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSandbox nil validation\n- **GIVEN** nil SandboxInfo\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** it returns an error indicating sandbox cannot be nil\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSandbox empty SessionID validation\n- **GIVEN** SandboxInfo with empty SessionID\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called\n- **THEN** it returns an error indicating session ID cannot be empty\n\n### Requirement: Connection lifecycle\nThe system SHALL properly manage Valkey connection lifecycle including initialization and cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: Close method\n- **GIVEN** an active Valkey connection\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** the Valkey client connection is closed\n\n### Requirement: Data structures\nThe system SHALL use appropriate data structures for efficient session management.\n\n#### Scenario: Session storage\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo to store\n- **WHEN** stored in Valkey\n- **THEN** the session data is stored with key prefix \"session:\"\n\n#### Scenario: Expiry index\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with expiry time\n- **WHEN** stored in Valkey\n- **THEN** the session ID is added to a sorted set with expiry time as score\n\n#### Scenario: Last activity index\n- **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with last activity time\n- **WHEN** stored in Valkey\n- **THEN** the session ID is added to a sorted set with last activity time as score\n\n### Requirement: Bulk operations\nThe system SHALL support efficient bulk retrieval operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Multiple session retrieval\n- **GIVEN** multiple session IDs\n- **WHEN** retrieving sandbox data for all sessions\n- **THEN** it uses MGET for efficient bulk retrieval\n- **AND** returns an array of SandboxInfo structs","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-codin